        "release_notes": {
            "en-US": "<b>Version 62.6.</b>\n\n1) At disabled/removed from Add-ons Manager, most of defaults are restored, except resizer.\n2) I fixed the problem that when resizing task view down, status bar moves down with task view.\n3) If not seeing status bar, adjust height with resizer at least level, So, now on, you can see status bar at the level.\n4) If adjusting each layout size, each layout size is restored.\n\nNovember 26 2020.\n\nFrom Sungho Hwang."
        },
        "reviewed": null,
        "url": "https://addons.thunderbird.net/en-US/thunderbird/addon/taskviewlayout/versions/62.6",
        "version": "62.6"
    },
    "default_locale": "en-US",
    "description": {
        "en-US": "<b>Version 62.6.</b> updated in 2020-11-27.\n1) I added upside layout of taskview in version 62.6 again.\n2) At disabled/removed from Add-ons Manager, most of defaults are restored, except resizer.\n3) I fixed the problem that when resizing task view down, status bar moves down with task view.\n4) If not seeing status bar, adjust height with resizer at least level, So, now on, you can see status bar at the level.\n5) If adjusting each layout size, each layout size is restored.\n\n<b>Please, use browserAction to put it at tabs toolbar in where browserAction is pinned.</b>\n\n praise Stephen Kim Sou-hwan.\n\n<b>[Notes]\n1) If not seeing status bar, please, resize task tree (right bottom edge of task tree).\n</b>\n\n<b>About all-day persistence of this program.</b>\nIf not closing operating system, please, use <b>Minimize on close</b>.",
        "ko": "<b>Please, use browserAction to put it at tabs toolbar in where browserAction is pinned.</b>\n\n praise Stephen Kim Sou-hwan.\n\n<b>[Notes]\nI removed a upside taskview in this version, because the functionality was not high.\n</b>\n\n<b>Horizontal level of taskview</b>\nAdjust horizontal level, <b>before clicking any button of browserAction.</b>\nIf so, during TaskviewLayout running time, horizontal level can be adjusted to that point."
    },
